# function to visualize class images
import cv2

def visualize_class(class_name):
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
    columns = 2
    rows = 1
    imgnames = list(data[data['label']==class_name].iloc[:2]['image_id'])
    for i in range(len(imgnames)):
        img_name = imgnames[i]
        im = cv2.imread(folder_path +'/'+ img_name)
        fig.add_subplot(rows, columns, int(i)+1)
        plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(im, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
        plt.title(class_name)

Oversampling & Undersampling Data¶

Since Class_3 has far more data than other classes, then we need to resolve this imbalance. So, I'll be doing an undersampling for class_3 with the same size of class_4 to get rid of all data larger than len(df_class_4)

In [13]:
# Divide by class
df_class_0 = data[data['label'] == '0']
df_class_1 = data[data['label'] == '1']
df_class_2 = data[data['label'] == '2']
df_class_3 = data[data['label'] == '3']
df_class_4 = data[data['label'] == '4']

#under-sampling
df_class_3_under = df_class_3.sample(len(df_class_4))
df_test_under = pd.concat([df_class_0,df_class_1,df_class_2,df_class_3_under,df_class_4], axis=0)

# save the new label & img_id to labels.csv
balanced_data = pd.DataFrame(df_test_under, columns=['image_id','label']).\
to_csv(folder_path + '/labels.csv',index=False)

# Creat Train / Val folders for each class
#  /cassava-leaf-diseases/train/0,1,2,3,4
# /cassava-leaf-diseases/valid/0,1,2,3,4


val_ratio = 0.15
test_ratio = 0.0
os.chdir(folder_path) 
root_dir = folder_path
classes_dir = ['0','1','2','3','4']

# if the folders don't exist, create (train and valid) folders for each class
if os.path.isdir('train') is False:
    for cls in classes_dir:
        os.makedirs('train/'+cls)
        os.makedirs('valid/'+cls)
        
        allFileNames = os.listdir(cls)
        np.random.shuffle(allFileNames)
        train_FileNames, val_FileNames, test_FileNames = np.split(np.array(allFileNames),
                                                              [int(len(allFileNames)* (1 - val_ratio - test_ratio)), 
                                                               int(len(allFileNames)* (1 - test_ratio))])

        train_FileNames = [cls+'/' + name for name in train_FileNames.tolist()]
        val_FileNames   = [cls+'/' + name for name in val_FileNames.tolist()]

        print('Total images: ', len(allFileNames))
        print('Training: ', len(train_FileNames))
        print('Validation: ', len(val_FileNames))

    # moving images to the new directory
        for name in train_FileNames:
            shutil.move(name, 'train/' + cls)
             
        for name in val_FileNames:
            shutil.move(name, 'valid/' + cls)
        
    print("Done!")
